nodes.title: Load VAE_Note
widgets_values: The Load VAE node can be used to load a specific VAE model, VAE models are used to encoding and decoding images to and from latent space. Although the Load Checkpoint node provides a VAE model alongside the diffusion model, sometimes it can be useful to use a specific VAE model.

nodes.title: Load_Checkpoint_Note
widgets_values:
The Load Checkpoint node can be used to load a diffusion model, diffusion models are used to denoise latents. 

This node will also provide the appropriate VAE and CLIP model.

Confirm that the model is loadinbg from your checkpoint folder by clicking on the checkpoint title.

nodes.title: CLIP Text Encode_Note
widgets_values:
The CLIP Text Encode node can be used to encode a text prompt using a CLIP model into an embedding that can be used to guide the diffusion model towards generating specific images.

We will use 2 of these in each workflow.
One for the positive prompt(green) and one for the negative prompt(red)

For LCM
Set 
Steps to 3 ~ 8
CFG to 1 ~ 3 (less than 2 will ignore the negative prompt)

nodes.title: Workflow_Note
widgets_values:
frames2frames_workflow

This workflow takes a series of imput frames and passes themthrough LoRAs and controlnets. The output is a matching number of diffused frames

This Workflow uses  Latent Consistency Model (LCM)
LCM is a rapid generation model for faster rendering

https://github.com/0xbitches/ComfyUI-LCM

nodes.title: Load Video Note
widgets_values:
This sets the:
video: input video path
frame_load_cap: the max number of frames to load
slect_every_nth: select every Nth frame WHER n = A number, this will speed up rendering as only every nth frame is processed and the rest are discarded

CLI Commands for extracting frames from video and compiling frames into video
FFMPEG required

Vid2Frames - filename_%NUMDIGITSd.FILETYPE -> myframes_%5d.png
ffmpeg -i "PATH_TO_FILE" "PATH_TO_OUTPUT_FOLDER\filename_%NUMDIGITSd.FILETYPE"
